Alistair Brownlee wins Olympics 2012 triathlon gold
Great Britain's Alistair Brownleewins the triathlon gold medalat the London 2012 Olympics in Hyde Park.Spain's Javier Gomez took silver, with Brownlee's brother Jonny winning bronze after serving a 15-second penalty for mounting his bike too early.The gold is Britain's 19th of the London Games, equalling the total number of golds they picked up in Beijing in 2008.Watch a replay of the men's triathlon on BBC Sport's Interactive Video Player.Available to UK users only.